    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Historical Flemish painting technique identified by Karel Van Mander: a flesh colored first layer of paint above the white ground providing the initial tone. It is visible as a substratum beneath the translucent layers of glaze. Primuersel is equivalent to the Italian imprimatura.</Note_Text>
